UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Amilcar BARROS-GOMEZ, a.k.a. Toty, a.k.a. El Negrito, a.k.a. Carlos Palmar, a.k.a. Robert Higius, Defendant-Appellant. No. 07-12571

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Nov. 26, 2007. Amilcar Barros-Gomez, Me Rae, GA, pro se. Patricia D. Barksdale, Jacksonville, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellee. *483Before BIRCH, DUBINA and BLACK, Circuit Judges. PER CURIAM:

David Mengers, appointed counsel for Amilear Barros-Gomez, has filed a motion to withdraw on appeal, supported by a brief prepared pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Our independent review of the record confirms counsel’s assessment of the relative merits of any potential issues for appeal. Because the record reveals no issues of arguable merit, we GRANT counsel’s motion to withdraw and AFFIRM Barros-Gomez’s conviction and sentence.
